    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Jewish Tipping Point</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Arthur Palgon letter on Samuel G Freedman's August 13 article on dispute among Jews in Beachwood, Ohio, hopes that choice of Joseph I Lieberman as vice-presidential candidate will lead American electorate to be more tolerant of Orthodox Jews (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Now that Joseph I. Lieberman has been picked as the vice-presidential candidate on the Democratic ticket, I hope that the American electorate will be more tolerant of Orthodox Jews than Si Wachsberger is (Samuel G. Freedman, Aug. 13). If Lieberman were living in Beachwood, Ohio, I'm certain he would be voting in favor of building the Orthodox campus.</p>
        <p>Arthur Palgon  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
